        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">CRITICAL ISSUES (3)</h2>
            
            <div class="warning" style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--warning-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h3 style="color: var(--warning-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">ISSUE #1: Exposed Cloudflare API Token in Repository</h3>
                
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Severity:</strong> CRITICAL (CVSS 9.1)</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Status:</strong> [ ] NOT STARTED | [ ] IN PROGRESS | [ ] COMPLETE | [ ] VERIFIED</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Assigned To:</strong> _________________ | <strong>Due Date:</strong> _________________</p>
                
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Description:</strong></p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Live Cloudflare API token committed to repository and visible in plaintext in configuration files.</p>
                
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Evidence (File Locations):</strong></p>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li>Comserv/config/cloudflare_config.json - Line 18</li>
                    <li>Comserv/config/api_credentials.json - Line 8</li>
                    <li>Token value exposed: cXPhJ9FFvNI6XcV7Xf-TxVI_IDC2zdlVPePa_n5w</li>
                </ul>
                
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Attack Vector:</strong></p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Attackers with repository access (cloned repo, developer machines, CI/CD logs) can modify DNS records for all managed domains, purge CDN cache, modify SSL settings, and create security policies.</p>
                
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Impact:</strong></p>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li>Unauthorized DNS modification (point domains to attacker servers)</li>
                    <li>SSL certificate changes</li>
                    <li>Denial of service via CDN manipulation</li>
                    <li>Cache poisoning attacks</li>
                    <li>Affects: computersystemconsulting.ca, beemaster.ca, helpdesk.computersystemconsulting.ca</li>
                </ul>
                
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Remediation Steps:</strong></p>
                <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li><strong>STEP 1 - Rotate Token (Within 24 hours):</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Log into Cloudflare account: https://dash.cloudflare.com/</li>
                            <li>Navigate to: Account Profile → API Tokens</li>
                            <li>Revoke token: cXPhJ9FFvNI6XcV7Xf-TxVI_IDC2zdlVPePa_n5w</li>
                            <li>Create new token with same permissions</li>
                            <li>Document new token (temporary location only)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>STEP 2 - Remove from Git History (Use git-filter-repo):</strong>
                        <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                            <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
# Install git-filter-repo
pip install git-filter-repo

# Remove sensitive data from ALL history
git filter-repo --replace-text <(echo 'cXPhJ9FFvNI6XcV7Xf-TxVI_IDC2zdlVPePa_n5w==<REDACTED>')

# Force push to update repository
git push origin --force --all
git push origin --force --tags
                            </code></pre>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>STEP 3 - Update Configuration Files:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Edit Comserv/config/cloudflare_config.json</li>
                            <li>Replace: "api_token" : "[REDACTED - REAL TOKEN MUST NOT BE COMMITTED]"</li>
                            <li>With: "api_token" : "[% ENV.CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN %]"</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>STEP 4 - Update .env Template:</strong>
                        <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                            <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
# Add to .env.example
CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=your_token_here
CLOUDFLARE_EMAIL=shantamcbain@gmail.com
                            </code></pre>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>STEP 5 - Update Perl Code to Load from Environment:</strong>
                        <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                            <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
# In CloudflareManager.pm or similar
my $api_token = $ENV{CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN} 
    or die "CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN environment variable not set";
                            </code></pre>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>STEP 6 - Verification:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Verify new token works: curl -H "Authorization: Bearer NEW_TOKEN" https://api.cloudflare.com/client/v4/user</li>
                            <li>Test in staging environment</li>
                            <li>Confirm old token is fully revoked</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ol>
                
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>References:</strong></p>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li>OWASP A7:2021 - Identification and Authentication Failures</li>
                    <li>CWE-798: Use of Hard-Coded Credentials</li>
                    <li>Cloudflare API Security: https://developers.cloudflare.com/api/</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="warning" style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--warning-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h3 style="color: var(--warning-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">ISSUE #2: Database Credentials in .env Files</h3>
                
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Severity:</strong> CRITICAL (CVSS 8.8)</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Status:</strong> [ ] NOT STARTED | [ ] IN PROGRESS | [ ] COMPLETE | [ ] VERIFIED</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Assigned To:</strong> _________________ | <strong>Due Date:</strong> _________________</p>
                
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Description:</strong></p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Plain text database credentials stored in .env files that are in version control or discoverable on systems.</p>
                
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Evidence (File Locations):</strong></p>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li>.env - DB_PASSWORD=comserv_pass, DB_ROOT_PASSWORD=rootpassword_dev, REDIS_PASSWORD=redispass_dev</li>
                    <li>Comserv/.env.development</li>
                    <li>Comserv/db_config.template.json (multiple password fields)</li>
                </ul>
                
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Impact:</strong></p>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li>Complete database access (read/write/delete all data)</li>
                    <li>Data exfiltration of all sites' information</li>
                    <li>Data destruction/ransomware attacks</li>
                    <li>Privilege escalation to root database user</li>
                </ul>
                
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Remediation Steps:</strong></p>
                <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li><strong>STEP 1 - Rotate All Database Passwords:</strong>
                        <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                            <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
# Log into MySQL/MariaDB as root
mysql -h 192.168.1.198 -u root -p

# Change application user password
ALTER USER 'comserv'@'%' IDENTIFIED BY 'NEW_STRONG_PASSWORD_HERE';

# Change root password
ALTER USER 'root'@'%' IDENTIFIED BY 'NEW_ROOT_PASSWORD_HERE';

# Flush privileges
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
                            </code></pre>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>STEP 2 - Remove .env from Git History:</strong>
                        <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                            <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
git filter-repo --path .env --invert-paths
git filter-repo --path .env.development --invert-paths
git filter-repo --path Comserv/.env --invert-paths
git filter-repo --path Comserv/.env.development --invert-paths
git push origin --force --all
                            </code></pre>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>STEP 3 - Ensure .gitignore Blocks These Files:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Verify .gitignore contains: .env, .env.*, !.env.example</li>
                            <li>Confirm template only (.env.example) is committed</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>STEP 4 - Deploy New Credentials Securely:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Use environment variables in Docker Compose</li>
                            <li>Use secrets management tool (HashiCorp Vault, AWS Secrets Manager, Kubernetes Secrets)</li>
                            <li>Pass via secure configuration at runtime</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>STEP 5 - Verification:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Test database connection with new credentials</li>
                            <li>Confirm application starts with new passwords</li>
                            <li>Verify old passwords no longer work</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <div class="warning" style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--warning-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h3 style="color: var(--warning-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">ISSUE #3: Weak Credential Obfuscation (Not Encryption)</h3>
                
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Severity:</strong> CRITICAL (CVSS 7.5)</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Status:</strong> [ ] NOT STARTED | [ ] IN PROGRESS | [ ] COMPLETE | [ ] VERIFIED</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Assigned To:</strong> _________________ | <strong>Due Date:</strong> _________________</p>
                
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Description:</strong></p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">ProxmoxCredentials module uses non-cryptographic obfuscation scheme that stores plaintext passwords with a hard-coded salt, providing no real security.</p>
                
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Evidence (File Locations):</strong></p>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Util/ProxmoxCredentials.pm - Lines 47-80</li>
                    <li>Hard-coded salt: 'ComservProxmoxSalt2025'</li>
                    <li>Obfuscation format: "OBFS:[hash]:[PLAINTEXT_PASSWORD]"</li>
                </ul>
                
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Issues:</strong></p>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li>Salt is hard-coded in source code (publicly available)</li>
                    <li>Plaintext password stored in the "obfuscated" value itself</li>
                    <li>No actual encryption - only string concatenation</li>
                    <li>False sense of security</li>
                </ul>
                
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Remediation Steps:</strong></p>
                <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li><strong>STEP 1 - Implement Proper Encryption:</strong>
                        <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                            <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
# In ProxmoxCredentials.pm, replace obfuscation with encryption

use Crypt::CBC;
use Digest::SHA qw(sha256);

sub encrypt_credential {
    my ($plaintext, $master_key) = @_;
    
    my $cipher = Crypt::CBC->new(
        -key    => sha256($master_key),
        -cipher => 'Cipher::AES',
        -header => 'salt'
    );
    
    return $cipher->encrypt_hex($plaintext);
}

sub decrypt_credential {
    my ($encrypted, $master_key) = @_;
    
    my $cipher = Crypt::CBC->new(
        -key    => sha256($master_key),
        -cipher => 'Cipher::AES',
        -header => 'salt'
    );
    
    return $cipher->decrypt_hex($encrypted);
}
                            </code></pre>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>STEP 2 - Migrate to Environment Variables:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Store master encryption key in environment variable</li>
                            <li>Load Proxmox credentials from secure vault at startup</li>
                            <li>Never persist credentials in files</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>STEP 3 - Update cpanfile Dependencies:</strong>
                        <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                            <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
requires 'Crypt::CBC';
requires 'Crypt::Cipher::AES';
                            </code></pre>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>STEP 4 - Verification:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Test encryption/decryption cycle</li>
                            <li>Verify Proxmox connections work with encrypted credentials</li>
                            <li>Confirm old obfuscation method is completely removed</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">HIGH SEVERITY ISSUES (5)</h2>
            
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid #ff9800; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h3 style="color: #ff9800; font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">ISSUE #4: Missing CSRF Protection</h3>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Severity:</strong> HIGH (CVSS 8.8) | <strong>Status:</strong> [ ] NOT STARTED | [ ] IN PROGRESS | [ ] COMPLETE</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Evidence:</strong> No CSRF token validation in Controllers (Admin.pm, User.pm, etc.) - Forms accept POST/PUT/DELETE without token verification</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Assigned To:</strong> _________________ | <strong>Due Date:</strong> _________________</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Reference:</strong> OWASP A4:2021 - Insecure Design | CWE-352</p>
            </div>

            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid #ff9800; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h3 style="color: #ff9800; font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">ISSUE #5: Hardcoded Admin User Bypass</h3>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Severity:</strong> HIGH (CVSS 7.2) | <strong>Status:</strong> [ ] NOT STARTED | [ ] IN PROGRESS | [ ] COMPLETE</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Evidence:</strong> Comserv/lib/Comserv/Util/AdminAuth.pm lines 60-70 - Usernames 'Shanta' and 'ai_assistant' bypass authorization checks</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Assigned To:</strong> _________________ | <strong>Due Date:</strong> _________________</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Reference:</strong> OWASP A1:2021 - Broken Access Control | CWE-284</p>
            </div>

            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid #ff9800; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h3 style="color: #ff9800; font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">ISSUE #6: Plaintext Passwords in Configuration Files</h3>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Severity:</strong> HIGH (CVSS 7.5) | <strong>Status:</strong> [ ] NOT STARTED | [ ] IN PROGRESS | [ ] COMPLETE</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Evidence:</strong> Comserv/comserv.conf - SMTP and Virtualmin passwords marked "Replace with actual password" but may contain real credentials</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Assigned To:</strong> _________________ | <strong>Due Date:</strong> _________________</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Reference:</strong> OWASP A7:2021 | CWE-798</p>
            </div>

            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid #ff9800; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h3 style="color: #ff9800; font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">ISSUE #7: Container Running as Root</h3>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Severity:</strong> HIGH (CVSS 7.0) | <strong>Status:</strong> [ ] NOT STARTED | [ ] IN PROGRESS | [ ] COMPLETE</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Evidence:</strong> Comserv/Dockerfile - Comment states "Don't switch to comserv user - entrypoint runs as root"</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Assigned To:</strong> _________________ | <strong>Due Date:</strong> _________________</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Reference:</strong> CIS Docker Benchmark | NIST SP 800-190</p>
            </div>

            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid #ff9800; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h3 style="color: #ff9800; font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">ISSUE #8: Sensitive Environment Variables in Docker Compose</h3>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Severity:</strong> HIGH (CVSS 6.5) | <strong>Status:</strong> [ ] NOT STARTED | [ ] IN PROGRESS | [ ] COMPLETE</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Evidence:</strong> docker-compose.yml passes DB_PASS_PROD in plaintext environment variables that may be logged</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Assigned To:</strong> _________________ | <strong>Due Date:</strong> _________________</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Reference:</strong> Docker Best Practices | OWASP A2:2021</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

